biography.text:
Tom Enzy is a multi-platinum DJ and producer from Portugal, with over 300 million streams and a global reputation in dance music. Starting his DJ journey at just five years old, he quickly gained recognition as "The Youngest DJ in the World."

Best known for his hit "Bololo" with Hugel, Tom has consistently dominated charts on Beatport and major DJ platforms. Ranked among the top DJs worldwide, he has collaborated with industry giants like Rick Ross, Flo Rida, and Bob Sinclar, releasing music on labels such as Sony, Universal, and Warner.

His high-energy performances have electrified festivals like Tomorrowland, Ultra Music Festival, and Fabrik Madrid. In 2022, he co-wrote the global hit "In the Dark" with Purple Disco Machine, topping charts and winning Best Producer of the Year at the BUMA Awards.

With a signature blend of tribal house, Latin, and urban sounds, Tom Enzy continues to push boundaries, solidifying his status as a leading force in electronic music.
